21.body: Looked at the language basics, it looks very similar to Rust. Can Contract B call Contract A if I don't have Contract A 's code?. FuelVM do not need to serialize data to pass between contracts; instead they simply pass a pointer to the data. This is because the FuelVM has a shared global memory [ The Sway Book - Differences from Ethereum ]
